id: pm-fbyu
title: "Add agent-identity dimension to telemetry events: surface PM_AUTHOR as hashed author_context"
description: "Telemetry events record source_context (user/automation/test/dogfood/audit_smoke) and session_id but carry no signal identifying agent-driven invocations vs. human CLI use within the 'automation' bucket. PM_AUTHOR (e.g. 'maintainer-agent', 'claude-code-agent') is already set on mutations; exposing a hashed derivative in telemetry payloads would allow Sentry/dashboard queries to segment agent-driven usage patterns, error rates, and latency without leaking the raw author string."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:observability","area:telemetry",privacy
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:03:35.109Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-18T14:34:46.988Z"
author: audit-observability-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- When PM_AUTHOR env var is a non-empty string, include a stable `author_context_hash` field (HMAC-SHA256, keyed on installation_id) in command_start and command_finish payloads at capture_level != minimal.\n- At minimal capture_level, include only a boolean `has_author_context: true/false`.\n- No raw PM_AUTHOR value is ever included.\n- SENSITIVE_KEYWORDS check is not needed (it's a hash); document this in a comment.\n- Unit test: same PM_AUTHOR value + same installation_id = same hash; different installation_id = different hash."
parent: pm-5oj5
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "command_start/command_finish payloads now carry an agent-identity dimension from PM_AUTHOR: author_context_hash (installation-keyed one-way hash) at redacted/max, has_author_context boolean at minimal; raw value never emitted."
expected_result: command_start/command_finish carry author_context_hash (non-minimal) or has_author_context (minimal) derived from PM_AUTHOR without leaking the raw value.
actual_result: Installation-keyed hash stability + cross-installation isolation verified; raw value never emitted; 100/100/100/100.
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-18T14:34:26.894Z",claude-code-agent,"Bundled with pm-3n3b/pm-gsoe (epic pm-5oj5). PM_AUTHOR surfaces as installation-id-keyed one-way author_context_hash (same construction as pm_root_hash/cwd_hash) at redacted/max capture, and only has_author_context boolean at minimal. Raw value never emitted; bypasses SENSITIVE_KEYWORDS by design (documented in code + TELEMETRY.md). Wired into command_start + command_finish."
files[3]{path,scope,note}:
  scripts/prod/telemetry/TELEMETRY.md,project,PM_AUTHOR agent-identity dimension documented
  src/core/telemetry/runtime.ts,project,buildAuthorContextPayloadFields + start/finish payload wiring
  tests/unit/core/telemetry/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts,project,installation-keyed hash stability coverage
close_reason: Shipped privacy-preserving PM_AUTHOR telemetry dimension with stability/installation-isolation coverage; 100/100/100/100.
body: "## Context\n\nFile: src/core/telemetry/runtime.ts lines 528-555 — resolveTelemetrySourceContext returns source_context. PM_AUTHOR env var is not read here.\n\nFile: src/core/telemetry/runtime.ts lines 818-871 — buildCommandStartPayload; no author_context field.\n\nThe source_context='automation' bucket currently conflates all non-TTY invocations: CI, MCP, agent loops, scripts. Hashing PM_AUTHOR (same HMAC-SHA256 keyed on installation_id as used for pm_root_hash) would be privacy-preserving but allow counting distinct agent types.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- When PM_AUTHOR env var is a non-empty string, include a stable `author_context_hash` field (HMAC-SHA256, keyed on installation_id) in command_start and command_finish payloads at capture_level != minimal.\n- At minimal capture_level, include only a boolean `has_author_context: true/false`.\n- No raw PM_AUTHOR value is ever included.\n- SENSITIVE_KEYWORDS check is not needed (it's a hash); document this in a comment.\n- Unit test: same PM_AUTHOR value + same installation_id = same hash; different installation_id = different hash.\n\n## Evidence\n\nsrc/core/telemetry/runtime.ts:52 — source_context values list; no 'agent' tier.\nsrc/core/telemetry/runtime.ts:859-870 — runtime object in payload; no PM_AUTHOR dimension."
